description.value: When someone pulls the trip wire, the urn smashes against a creature in the doorway, making a shattering urn Strike against that creature, then releases a viper into the square that contained the trap. The viper attacks any non-plant creature it detects.

10 feet. A creature entering the aura or starting its turn in the aura must succeed at a @Check[type:fortitude|dc:14] save or become @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.AJh5ex99aV6VTggg]{Flat-Footed} for 1 round (and @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.xYTAsEpcJE1Ccni3]{Slowed 1} for 1 round on a critical failure). A creature that succeeds at its save is temporarily immune for 1 minute.

The foul smell emitted by a stinkweed shambler becomes stronger when its leaves are crushed or burned. When a stinkweed shambler takes bludgeoning or fire damage, the DC for its Stench ability increases to 18 and its Stealth bonus decreases to +4. Both of these effects last for 1 minute.
The stinkweed shambler Strides up to half its Speed. This movement doesn't provoke reactions.
A stinkweed shambler ignores difficult terrain and greater difficult terrain from non-magical foliage.
